I believe the naming convention changed (CCing @yifeif @gunan to confirm) between 0.11 and 0.12, but the URLs of the earlier releases are still accessible. For example:

  • 0.11.0rc0: https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/gpu/tensorflow-0.11.0rc0-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl
  • 0.11.0: https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/gpu/tensorflow-0.11.0-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl

Closing this out as the URLs are still accessible. Let me know if I misunderstood.

I believe the naming convention changed (CCing @yifeif @gunan  to confirm) between 0.11 and 0.12, but the URLs of the earlier releases are still accessible. For example:

- 0.11.0rc0: `https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/gpu/tensorflow-0.11.0rc0-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl`
- 0.11.0:`
https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/gpu/tensorflow-0.11.0-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl`

Closing this out as the URLs are still accessible. Let me know if I misunderstood.
